cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.THEORY, cs.FL. 

The paper introduces a novel type system for resource analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) or theory (cs.THEORY) sub-categories. The focus on amortised complexity and self-adjusting data structures suggests that it could also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or algorithms (cs.AL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of potential functions and automatable analysis suggests that it could belong to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) or formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) sub-categories.
